Distributed version control system

## Config

Prepare:

    git config user.name "My name"
    git config user.email my@email
    
    git config --list   # Show configs

Alias:

    git config --global alias.uncommit 'reset HEAD^'

## Use

Basic use:

    git init
    git add file.txt
    git status
    git commit -m "Message"

Commit:

    git commit -a   # Commit all changes

Stash:

    git stash      # Save the stash
    git stash pop  # Apply and delete the stash

    git stash apply
    git stash list
    git stash drop stash@{0}

## Undo

Remove from stage:

    git add file
    git reset file

Remove last commit while keeping files intact:

    git reset HEAD^

## Advanced

Modify author info in all commits:

    git filter-branch --env-filter '
        # You can use shell script code here
        export GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="Now author name"
        export GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="author@example.com"
    ' --tag-name-filter cat -- --branches --tags

This leaves a original branch without modifications under `refs/original/*`.
Once you review your filtered changes and you are ok with them, you can erase the backup branch:

    git update-ref -d refs/original/refs/heads/master
